{"tid":1938213,"cid":5,"subCid":10,"title":"(疫情) 美國最大戲院商: 每星期蝕3000萬美元","createTime":"2020-03-22T11:37:39.000Z","updateTime":"2020-03-22T15:06:27.000Z","uid":134071,"like":155,"dislike":2,"uniUserReply":43,"replies":[{"pid":"008bd8494cd0643297ab49096cadfb406d98d18c","tid":1938213,"uid":134071,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-22T11:37:39.000Z","msg":"(<strong>AMC</strong>係美國最大戲院商, 但呢間公司係<strong>中資: 中國萬達佔38%股份, 係最大股東</strong>)<br />\n<br />\n美國最大戲院商AMC: 在疫情之下, AMC每星期蝕3000萬-4000萬美元<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.mediaplaynews.com/amc-theatres-ceo-we-dont-have-a-penny-of-revenue-coming-in/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mediaplaynews.com%2Famc-theatres-ceo-we-dont-have-a-penny-of-revenue-coming-in%2F&d=BTQ0Nb6fQhXLRDVXZ5xLdJR%2B4kUINcy65scadR%2F1ewI%3D&h=4028834b\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.mediaplaynews.com/amc-theatres-ceo-we-dont-have-a-penny-of-revenue-coming-in/</a><br />\n<br />\nSpeaking to CNN, <strong>Adam Aron, CEO of AMC</strong>, said the chain literally does not have &ldquo;a penny of revenue&rdquo; coming in.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;Three weeks ago, AMC was an immensely healthly company,&rdquo; Aron said. &ldquo;And now with expenses out the door and no revenue, we are burning through cash and the liquidity we need, only the [federal] government is going to provide that.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nIn 2019, AMC Entertainment generated $5.5 billion in revenue with $770 million in pre-tax earnings. <strong>This week alone, Aron said the chain would spend $30-to-$40 million dollars just to stay in business. An amount, he said, that would continue weekly as the quarantine period continues.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;Our revenues this week are zero,&rdquo; Aron said.</strong>"},{"pid":"2203648ecd94277f7b9870e1062b8528cf4cfba1","tid":1938213,"uid":134071,"like":45,"dislike":1,"score":44,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-03-22T11:37:57.000Z","msg":"萬達又輸<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" 